      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role (A88–A89):</strong> the king's tiefling stepbrother — Ileosa's poison-tool and first victim, walled up alive behind his own card-room (his bones lie at <strong>A11</strong>). <strong>The castle's kindest ghost and best informant:</strong> at A89 he can barely manifest (a misty horned old man rising from a harrow deck) until his bones are recovered — Zellara senses where they lie. Restored, he testifies that <strong>Ileosa poisoned King Eodred II</strong> (and that he shares the guilt), names her ritual — the <strong>Everdawn Pool</strong> in the <strong>Sunken Queen</strong>, fed by the lifeblood of thousands — and points the PCs to Domina's study (<strong>A90</strong>). See the A89 entry for his and Zellara's farewell gift.</p>",
